What is GitOps?
GitOps is a DevOps practice where:
Git is the single source of truth
Kubernetes manifests (YAML files) are stored in Git
Any change in Git automatically updates the cluster

What is ArgoCD?
ArgoCD is a GitOps tool that continuously syncs Kubernetes cluster state with the desired state defined in Git.

argocd components:
-------------------
1)API Server (argocd-server): The entry point of ArgoCD. Everything you do —
                            UI login, CLI command, clicking sync — goes through API Server.
2)Repository Server (argocd-repo-server): Repository Server = Git Reader + Manifest Generator
                                        It: Connects to Git
                                           Pulls the latest code
                                           Converts Helm/Kustomize into plain Kubernetes YAML
                                           Sends that desired state to Application Controller
                                           It does NOT deploy anything.
3)Application Controller (argocd-application-controller): The ArgoCD Application Controller is the core component responsible for continuously comparing
                                                        the desired state of applications defined in Git with the live state in the Kubernetes cluster.
4)What is Drift?
-------------
Drift = Difference between:
Git YAML → says replicas: 3
Cluster → currently running 1 pod
ArgoCD detects this mismatch.
If auto-sync is enabled → it fixes automatically.

Complete Flow in Simple Words
--------------------------------
Developer pushes YAML to Git
Repo Server pulls YAML
Application Controller compares with cluster
If mismatch → Sync
API Server shows status in UI
Redis improves performance

                                     Step-by-Step Installation (Real-Time Method)
                                     --------------------------------------------
Step 1: Create Namespace 
command: kubectl create namespace argocd
Step 2: Install ArgoCD
command: kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml
         kubectl get pods -n argocd ( All pods should be Running.)
 Step 3: Access ArgoCD UI
 ------------------------
 Option 1: Port Forward (Local Testing)
 command: kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443
 https://localhost:8080
 
 Step 4: Get Initial Password
 command: kubectl get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -n argocd -o yaml
 Decode password:
 command: echo <base64-password> | base64 --decode
 username : admin password: use that decode password

                           Production Access (LoadBalancer Method)
                           -----------------------------------------
command; kubectl patch svc argocd-server -n argocd -p '{"spec": {"type": "LoadBalancer"}}'
       This command modifies the existing Kubernetes Service named argocd-server in the argocd namespace and changes its service type to LoadBalancer, 
       so it becomes externally accessible.
       Check external IP:
       -----------------
       kubectl get svc -n argocd
